nodes.title: Note 7: KSampler
widgets_values: Let denoise on 0.35 and only use the "Control Net - strenght" for "creativity"

nodes.title: Note 4: Prompt
widgets_values:
To upscale, just change the prompt to what ever you want.
To avoid eyes, mouthes and noses or stuff like this in bigger images, i would recommend to use only materials like above.

No worry, there are two CLIP Text Encoder because i like to change it between those two.

nodes.title: Note 5: Tiled Diffusion
widgets_values:
If you get an error, it could be that your image is to small.
Set Tile_width / Tile_height then to: 512

After that put it back to 1024.

nodes.title: Note 1: Control Panel
widgets_values:
Controlpanel:
Use the Upscale "Yes/No" to apply the whole Upscale process.
Turn it off if you want to prepare your image before upscaling.

To disable the background fix, just set it on "No".

nodes.title: Note 8: IPAdapter
widgets_values:
If you try to get a specific Style, try to apply IPAdapter. 

For normal upscaling with prompting i recommend to turn it off!

nodes.title: Note 3: ControlNet
widgets_values:
Inpaint as control net + the normal upscaled image as reference.

Lower Strenght = More Creativity 
Higher Strenght = Less Creativity

I would recommend for 1-2k images size 0.2 for creativity.
After that 0.3-0.4 to get less distortion .
